{
    "analysis": "We have global thresholds (P50/P90/P95) for each (cmdb_id, kpi_name) time series of the five candidate services computed from the full available series. Timestamp coverage shows point granularity from ~2024-01-23 12:02 to 12:26 UTC and most series have ~24–25 points. Next, per the workflow we must filter the metric data to the incident window (2024-01-23 11:59:43 to 2024-01-23 12:29:43 UTC) and detect anomalies by comparing per-(cmdb_id,kpi_name) points to the previously computed global thresholds (use P95 as primary threshold for resource KPIs where higher is worse). We'll then identify which service KPIs show consecutive anomalies during the incident window.",
